The '''Fundación Española para la Ciencia y la Tecnología (FECYT)''' (English: Spanish Foundation for Science and Technology) is  an independent nonprofit organization in Spain that promotes [[Science and technology in Spain|Spanish science and technology]].<ref>{{citation |url=https://www.openaire.eu/project-partners/ |accessdate= 8 July 2018 |title= FECYT (Fundación Española para la Ciencia y Tecnología -Spanish Foundation for Science and Technology) |work=Project Partners |publisher=[[OpenAIRE]] }}</ref> It formed in 2001, and receives funding from the national [[Ministerio de Ciencia, Innovación y Universidades]] (former Ministerio de Educación y Ciencia).<ref>{{citation |title=Health and Medical Research in Spain |author=Fragiskos Archontakis |url= https://www.rand.org/content/dam/rand/pubs/documented_briefings/2009/RAND_DB566.pdf |publisher=[[RAND Europe]] |year= 2009 }}</ref>

